Measurements (mm): TL 17.0; HW 4.3; 
PL
4.2; MPW 1.6; SDW 2.5; CL 4.3; FL 5.3; 
MFW
2.3; WL 17.1.

Head (
Fig. 2C
): Transverse, 1.7 times wider than pronotal supracoxal dilation; vertex nearly straight, vertical process of vertex conical, short and blackish, 1.3 times higher than wide; juxta-ocular tubercles conical, black; eyes oval-shaped with a short distinct apical spine; frontal shield transverse, pentagonal, about 3.1 times wider than high, apex with a very short spike.

Pronotum (
Fig. 3C
): Rhomboidal, 1.7 times longer than wide; prozone shorter than metazone, disc with two flattened median tubercles, lateral margins with three, small dark tubercles on each side; metazone with a longitudinal median carina, lateral margins with some small dark tubercles.

