3.3; WL 16.4.

Head (
Fig. 2I
): Transverse, vertex nearly straight, process of vertex triangular, juxta-ocular tubercles small, conical; frontal shield transverse, with a tubercle on its upper margin; eyes oval-shaped with a short apical spine.

Pronotum (
Fig. 4C
): Rhomboidal, 1.6 times longer than wide; prozone stout and arched, disc with two flattened bumps, metazone longer than prozone, with a longitudinal median carina, lateral margins with some tubercles, lateral margins of supracoxal dilation forming an obtuse angle.
